§ VALIDATION  (reimpl-from-spec gate at LoA-content-level)

  § THESIS
    LoA-impl-divergence-from-this-spec triggers same reimpl-validation
    discipline as Substrate (§§ 30 § VALIDATION).

  § REIMPL-CONTRACTS
    R-LoA-1 : main() entry-point shape per § GAME-LOOP § ENTRY-POINT
    R-LoA-2 : initial-consent-flow per § GAME-LOOP § INITIAL-CONSENT-FLOW
    R-LoA-3 : World hierarchy (Labyrinth → Floor → Level → Room) preserved
    R-LoA-4 : Player + Companion archetypes per § WORLD-MODEL
    R-LoA-5 : ConsentZones gate intense-content per § PLAYER-MODEL
    R-LoA-6 : ApockalypseEngine state-shape per § APOCALYPSE-ENGINE
              (content TBD ; structure stable)
    R-LoA-7 : Companion-AI sovereignty per § AI-INTERACTION
    R-LoA-8 : audit-chain entries per phase / interaction / withdrawal
    R-LoA-9 : SaveJournal preserves Ω-tensor per §§ 18_ORTHOPERSIST

  § ORACLE-MODES (LoA-specific)
    @audit_test    : ConsentZone-bypass = compile-error or runtime-fault
    @audit_test    : Companion-coercion-shape = compile-error
    @replay        : LoA-session bit-exact-replay on same-(seed, choices)
    @hot_reload_test : Ω-tensor preserved across LoA hot-reload
    @golden        : narrative-text matches authored-canonical-text
    @property      : ∀ ConsentZone X ⇒ revoking-token ⇒ alt-path-offered

